article.headline: Stanford holds Bond to just seven points
article.linkText: No. 2 Stanford clamps down on Missouri
article.story:
COLUMBIA, Mo. (AP) -- Brooke Smith scored 16 points and Kelley
Suminski added 13 on her 22nd birthday, leading No. 2 Stanford to a
71-55 victory against Missouri on Saturday.

Smith took over inside in the second half, shooting 6-for-8 for
Stanford (8-0).

Megan Roney led Missouri (4-5) with 13 points. LaToya Bond, the
Tigers' second-leading scorer (12.9), was scoreless in the first
half and finished with seven points.

Leading 29-21 at halftime, the Cardinal scored 15 of the next 21
points, including eight from Smith. A 13-0 run later pushed
Stanford's lead to 60-31. Missouri used a 15-5 run to narrow the
gap.

Stanford entered the game allowing 48.3 points per game, the
third fewest in the country. The Cardinal limited the Tigers to
35-percent shooting and outrebounded them 45-23.

Candice Wiggins added 12 points and Kristen Newlin 11 for the
Cardinal.

Tiffany Brooks, a transfer from Kansas State, played her first
game for Missouri. She scored six points on 3-for-15 shooting in 33
minutes.
